<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-09-17T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-09-17T13:00:00-05:00" n="911" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d911">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/13222a.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Brazilian Minister</gloss>
                                to Mexico.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-09-17T13:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">September 17, 1914, 1 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Our telegram No. 246 of 15th answered your inquiry of same date relative
                            to evacuation. Please discourage any immediate requests for recognition.
                            You will be advised whenever the President feels the time is ripe for
                            such action.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>